From: sKy <29267720+sKyissKy@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: phy: allow custom LED names via DT

The of_phy_led() function sets devname_mandatory = true, which forces
the MDIO device name (e.g., "mdio-bus:0f") as a prefix in every PHY
LED name. This makes the LED names hard to read and device-specific.

Set devname_mandatory to false so that DT label or color+function
properties can be used directly as the LED name, matching the behavior
of GPIO LEDs. Boards that want the devname prefix can still include it
in the label property.

Signed-off-by: sKy <29267720+sKyissKy@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/net/phy/phy_device.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/phy/phy_device.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/phy_device.c
@@ -3301,7 +3301,7 @@ static int of_phy_led(struct phy_device *phydev,
 	cdev->max_brightness = 1;
 	init_data.devicename = dev_name(&phydev->mdio.dev);
 	init_data.fwnode = of_fwnode_handle(led);
-	init_data.devname_mandatory = true;
+	init_data.devname_mandatory = false;
 
 	err = led_classdev_register_ext(dev, cdev, &init_data);
 	if (err)
